“Webhooks ensure backend consistency, SSE ensures great user experience.”
Use webhook for backend server to server communication, sse when real time ui updates are needed.
Webhook works even when client is not active.

“I use webhooks for backend-to-backend communication where reliability and retries are important, such as payment confirmations. I use SSE for real-time frontend updates like showing live payment status or dashboards. In production systems, both are often used together—webhooks update the backend, and SSE pushes updates to the UI.”


TCP (Transmission Control Protocol)
Connection oriented protocol that ensures reliable and ordered data delivery.
(Payment System, text messages)

UDP (User Datagram Protocol)
Connectionless protocol that sends data without guarantee of delivery or order, faster than TCP.
(Live Streaming, Voice/video)

What happens when you click a url?
When you enter the url, the browser finds the server using DNS lookup, then browser connects to server
using TCP (SYNC->SYNC-ACK->ACK), TLS Handshake for HTTPS (secure connection, certificate validation,
encryption keys exchanged), sends http request, server process request, sends response and finally browser renders page.

URL → DNS → TCP → TLS → Request → Response → Render


